Discuss the functionality of the format() function in Python and its importance in string formatting. Illustrate with an example.

The format() function in Python is used for string formatting, allowing you to insert values into a string in a specified format. It provides a flexible and powerful way to create strings with placeholders that are replaced by values dynamically.

The general syntax of the format() function is as follows:

formatted_string = "template_string".format(value1, value2, ...)
